<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan to Receive 600m Dollars from IMF: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Minister for
Finance Ishaq Dar said here Thursday that Pakistan will receive
600 million U.S. dollars from the International Monetary Fund
(IMF) before the end of January, 1999.
</P>
<P>
Talking to newsmen, Dar said the IMF Board will be meeting
around January 15, 1999 and the World Bank meeting is expected a
week later to finalize the package for Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The Paris Club, he said, will be meeting in the last week of
next month to consider Pakistan's requirements for economic
assistance.
</P>
<P>
Dar said that by the close of 1998 calendar year Thursday,
Pakistan's foreign exchange reserves stand at 1.057 billion
dollars even after making 60 million dollar payments to the
preferred creditors.
</P>
<P>
As for the introduction of Euro currency from Friday, the
minister said the State Bank of Pakistan has been authorized to
include Euro currency in the country's authorized currency.
</P>
<P>
The government will be making certain changes during the next
few days in the light of the new development, he added.
</P>
<P>
Answering a question, Dar said the introduction of Euro will
not have any negative effect on Pakistan. On the contrary, the
European countries are reducing interest rate from 3.5 percent to
three percent with the launching of Euro currency Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
