<HEADLINE> Shanghai's 1998 Stock Trade Volume Nearly 3.5 Trillion Yuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Stock Exchange
(SSE), one of China's two exchanges, reported today a total trade
volume of 3.43 trillion yuan (about 400 million U.S. dollars) for
1998.
</P>
<P>
This figure, a 15 percent increase from last year, includes
1.24 trillion yuan from share trading, 2.12 trillion yuan from
state bond trading, and 60.5 billion yuan from fund trading,
according to latest statistic.
</P>
<P>
The SSE Composite Index closed the year at 1146.70 points, down
3.97 percent from one year earlier, with the year's highest
reaching 1422.98 points and the lowest standing at 1043.02 points.
</P>
<P>
The SSE 30 Index, which is based on 30 blue chips selected from
more than 300 A-shares available for domestic investors, finished
this year at 2759.87 points today.
</P>
<P>
The SSE A-shares for domestic investors had raised funds worth
36.99 billion yuan in 1998, while B-shares for overseas investors
had raised a total of 118 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1998, the SSE has 333 members and 87 B-share
brokers, including 38 from overseas.
</P>
<P>
Altogether 477 stocks are listed on the bourse a with total
market capitalization of 1.06 trillion yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
