<HEADLINE> Power Generator on Central China River Operational </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, December 31 (Xinhua) -- The first power generator on
the Xiangjiang River in central China's Hunan Province, one of the
State key projects for river power engineering, began operating
today.
</P>
<P>
The project includes four generators, each with a capacity of
30,000 kw, at a total cost of 1.89 billion yuan (about 230 million
U.S. dollars), of which 90 million dollars are from World Bank
loans.
</P>
<P>
After completion, the project will have the ability to generate
556 million kwh a year.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the project has considerably improved
navigation, now allowing ships of weights up to 1,000 tons to sail
this 180-kilometer-long stretch of the river. The docks along this
section also opened for navigation today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
