<HEADLINE> Simitis: Greece Will Realize its Goals in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Greece would realize the goals
it had set in 1999, which would see the start of planning for a
new four-year period, Greece's Prime Minister Costas Simitis said
in a new year message Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Simitis said that the sacrifices and efforts of the previous
year were taking boot and the first results of the economy were
tangible in thousands of large and small projects being undertaken
through Greece, in the increase in the real incomes of the Greek
people and in the role Greece was playing in the Balkans and the
European Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
This would be a four-year period which would allow Greeks to
make an even greater step, to increase prosperity, to proceed to a
juster distribution of the wealth produced to more citizens,
particularly those in need, he added.
</P>
<P>
He described 1998 as a good year, saying that the international
financial crisis had not harmed the Greek economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
