<HEADLINE> France Fixes Rate between Euro and Pacific Franc </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 31 (Xinhua) -- France Thursday fixed the
exchange rate between the euro and the Pacific franc, which is
used in New Caledonia and French Polynesia, at 1,000 Pacific franc
for 8.38 euros.
</P>
<P>
The council of finance ministers of 11 countries in the euro
zone decided on Thursday the rates of conversion between euro and
national currencies. The rate between euro and the French franc is
one for 6.559.
</P>
<P>
The conversion rate between the French franc and the Pacific
franc is one for 0.055.
</P>
<P>
The euro will also be introduced to the French overseas
departments of Martinique, Quadeloupe, Reunion and Guyana.
</P>
<P>
New Caledonia and French Polynesia are France's overseas
territories.  
</P>
</TEXT>
