<HEADLINE> French FM to Talk with Cambodian Counterpart </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 31 (Xinhua) -- French Foreign Minister Hubert
Vedrine will meet on Monday in Paris with his Cambodian
counterpart Hor Nahmong, said the foreign ministry on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"This meeting will allow us survey the bilateral relations and
the international aid to Cambodia," said foreign ministry
spokeswoman Anne Gazeau-Secret.
</P>
<P>
Hor Nahmong, who was former Cambodian ambassador in Paris, will
also meet with Minister of Cooperation Charles Josselin, she said.
</P>
<P>
France, together with Britain and the United States, has asked
for the putting on trial of two former leaders of the Khmer Rouge,
Kieu Samphan and Huon Chea, who surrendered themselves to the
government of Phnom Penh last week.
</P>
<P>
But Cambodian Prime Minister Hun Sen said he preferred to "bury
the past" and pardon the two men.  
</P>
