<HEADLINE> U.N. Donates Anti-Malaria Drugs to Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 31 (Xinhua) -- The World Health
Organization Thursday donated anti-malaria medicines worth about
180,000 U.S. Dollars to the Ethiopian health ministry.
</P>
<P>
The donation is in response to a recent appeal made by the
ministry for assistance in its bid to contain malaria epidemic
which is reportedly affected some 100 districts in the country
this year.
</P>
<P>
According to an earlier announcement by the Ethiopian health
ministry, some 100 districts were hit by malaria epidemic this
year and traditional safer areas including Addis Ababa have also
been hit by the epidemic as a result of changes in weather
conditions.
</P>
<P>
The anti-malaria medicines will be distributed to all parts of
the country which were hit by the epidemic.
</P>
<P>
About 40 million of Ethiopia's 58 million people live in
malaria- prone localities. An estimated two million people in the
country are affected by malaria every year. 
</P>
