<HEADLINE> Ice, Fog Cause Car Accidents in Northern Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Ice and fog Thursday caused two
car accidents involving a total of 25 cars in the northern part of
Greece.
</P>
<P>
A 15-car pile up on the Thessaloniki-Moudanion national road
was caused due to fog while ice was blamed for causing a 10-car
pile up on the Thessaloniki-Peraias road, said the semi-official
Athens News Agency (ANA) Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, fog also caused Thursday delays in flights at the
Thessaloniki international airport, which was closed due to fog on
Wednesday for the second time this week.
</P>
<P>
Car accidents kill some 3,000 people and injure about 30,000 in
Greece every year. 
