<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Encouraged by the prospect that
the Thai economy will be able to recover, new businesses in the
country are likely to be revived next year, the Commercial
Registration Department said.
</P>
<P>
More new companies are expected to be registered next year as
the private sector has growing confidence in the country's
economic recovery, the Thai News Agency reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
