Economists expect the Thai economy to recover in the second
half of next year, posting a 0.5 or 1 percent growth.
</P>
<P>
Not only the private sector but also foreign investors are
inquiring the department about the progress of the foreign
business law amendments.
</P>
<P>
The amendment of the law is expected to be concluded next year.
</P>
<P>
Among interested foreign businesses is Mercedes-Benz which
wants to use Thailand as its production base for exports. Other
investors include those from computer, telecommunication and
security service businesses. 
</P>
