<HEADLINE> Indian Trade Deficit Reaches 6.7 Billion US Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 1 (Xinhua) -- India's trade deficit for
April to November 1998 is estimated at 6.7 billion U.S. dollars
doubling that of 3.3 billion in the corresponding period of 1997,
said the latest official trade data released here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The country's exports during April to November 1998 are
estimated at 21.5 billion dollars which is 3.97 percent lower than
22.36 billion dollars in April to November 1997. Imports during
April to November, 1998 are estimated at 28.2 billion dollars
which is 9.5 percent higher than 25.7 billion dollars in the same
period in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The exports registered negative four percent growth and imports
rose by 9.5 percent during April-November this fiscal year (April
1, 1998-March 31, 1999). 
