<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 1 (Xinhua) -- China's tourism industry is
expected to receive a big boost with the introduction of its
Eco-Tour 1999 campaign beginning today.
</P>
<P>
As the theme of the tourism industry this year, Eco-Tour 1999
will comprise more than 30 festivals and ten other programs
including trips to explore the desert and protect the environment,
and bicycles and raft outings.
</P>
<P>
A ceremony to mark the start of China Eco-Tour '99 was held in
the famous tourist city of Guilin in southern China today.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by the National Tourism Administration, the State
Environmental Protection Administration, the State Forestry
Administration and the Chinese Academy of Sciences, the campaign
will feature more environment-friendly tours while helping to
achieve sustained growth for the tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
China greeted 62.5 million overseas visitors in 1998 and earned
12.5 billion U.S. dollars in foreign exchanges, up 8.5 percent and
3.5 percent from the previous year, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Some 659 million Chinese people took tours last year, bringing
the tourism sector 239 billion yuan in earnings, up 2.4 percent
and more than 13 percent from the previous year, respectively.
