<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Commentary: Indian Minister's Utterance on Taiwan Dangerous </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 1 (Xinhua) -- The utterance by Indian Urban
Development Minister Ram Jethmalani on Taiwan last Sunday was
evil-minded and dangerous as it was preaching recognition of the
island province of China.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with The Week magazine, the Indian minister
said that there is "a strong case" for recognition of Taiwan as
it is an "independent and democratic country now having 25
million people with a foreign exchange reserve of 96 billion U.S.
dollars."
</P>
<P>
Jethmalani, as a minister of India, should not be ignorant of
the simple fact that there is only one China in the world, Taiwan
is an inalienable part of China and the government of the
People's Republic of China is the sole legitimate government of
the country.
</P>
<P>
This has been accepted by the United Nations and the
international community as a fact. All countries declared their
commitment to pursuing the one-China policy when they established
diplomatic relations with China. In this case, India is no
exception.
</P>
<P>
Jethmalani's yearnings reveal that there is a force in India
that is opposing the improvement of Sino-Indian relations and
attempting to split China.
</P>
<P>
The Indian minister's remarks on Taiwan were a flagrant
interference in China's internal affairs and it was a grave
development aimed at splitting China. So it has naturally caused
indignation among the Chinese people, who have heighten their
vigilance.
</P>
<P>
The Taiwan issue is purely an internal affair of China and
China will never allow any foreign forces to meddle in its
internal affairs in whatever forms and under whatever
pretexts.
</P>
<P>
It is a common aspiration of all the Chinese people, including
the Taiwanese, to reunify the motherland as early as possible and
the reunification is an irresistible historical trend.
</P>
<P>
Jethmalani's utterance have seriously hurt the feelings of the
Chinese people and set obstacles to the improvement of relations
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
In the interview, the Indian minister also called on New Delhi
to "make a serious departure from its present thinking to get
back its land occupied in the 1962 Chinese aggression."
</P>
<P>
History has already drawn its conclusion on the 1962
India-China border clashes, which were caused by India's
expansionism. The fact is that India grabbed about 90,000 square
kilometers of Chinese territory.
</P>
<P>
When Indian armed forces launched large-scale attacks on
Chinese frontier troops in October 1962, China was forced to
mount a self-defensive counterattack.
</P>
<P>
Over the years, the Chinese government has been making efforts
for a peaceful solution to the border dispute and trying hard to
create favorable conditions for the enhancement of mutual
confidence between the two countries so as to bring out a
reasonable and final settlement of the border dispute.
</P>
<P>
Jethmalani's remarks on the border issue represented nothing
but a futile attempt to distort historical facts.
</P>
<P>
China and India are close neighbors and the two most populous
countries in the world. Currently, both countries are faced with
the task of boosting their economic development.
</P>
<P>
A friendly Sino-Indian relationship not only conforms to the
fundamental interests of the two countries and the two peoples
but also is conducive to the peace, stability and development in
Asia and the whole world.
</P>
<P>
History shows that as long as the two countries follow the
principles of peaceful coexistence, China and India will witness
a smooth development of their relations. Otherwise, the
Sino-Indian ties will suffer setbacks.
</P>
<P>
The Indian government should take due steps to get the
China-India ties back to the track of normal development by
removing obstacles from the way. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
