<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pak PM Satisfied with Karachi's Situation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif
has expressed his satisfaction over the law and order situation in
the southern port city of Karachi, saying it has registered a lot
of improvement and is gaining ground satisfactorily.
</P>
<P>
Talking to the media at the Governor House after presiding over
a high-level meeting in Karachi Friday to review the law and order
situation there, Sharif said that results are being achieved, and
peace is gradually returning to Karachi.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister was quoted by the Associated Press of
Pakistan as saying the actions taken so far are having a good
impact and the local administration and police are performing
well.
</P>
<P>
"I am satisfied that the accused involved in high profile cases
have been arrested. Their arrest alone gives a proof of the police
performance," he said, adding the administration, too, is playing
a better part in the whole exercise.
</P>
<P>
He said the decisions by the Military Courts, which were
established on November 20 last year, have started coming out and
culprits are being given punishment for their evil deeds.
</P>
<P>
Sharif said that not only in Karachi but also in the whole
country the law and order should be maintained with expeditious
decisions so that culprits are not only taken to task and awarded
due punishment but the common and suffering people could also
heave a sigh of relief.
</P>
<P>
Sharif said that as he is getting feed back the confidence of
the people in Karachi is now building up. Business activity is
improving, which would lead to more investment and bring an end to
unemployment.  
</P>
