<HEADLINE> China's Working Forces Shrinking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 1 (Xinhua) -- The number of staff and workers
in China declined by the end of September of 1998, according to
figures released by the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
Total staff and workers at the end of September amounted to
143.3 million, 3.57 million fewer than at the same time in 1997,
and the number of workers in the state sector declined by 3.1
percent to 105 million.
</P>
<P>
Northeast China's Liaoning Province, one of the country's major
industrial bases, saw the greatest decline in working
forces. Total staff and workers in Liaoning at the end of
September amounted to 9.25 million, 546,000 fewer on an annual
basis.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the non-state sector employed 11 million people,
1.56 million more than the same 1997 period.  
</P>
</TEXT>
