increase in total wage bill of staff and workers in the first nine
months of 1998, according to the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
Total wage bill of staff and workers in Tibet between January
and September amounted to 1.34 billion yuan, growing 24.4 percent
over the same period of 1997.
</P>
<P>
The national total during this period reached 669 billion yuan,
up 3.4 percent on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
Southeast China's Fujian Province ranked second in its wage
bill growth of staff and workers, with the amount hitting some 20
billion yuan, up 13 percent over the same period of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Northeast China's Jilin Province had the country's biggest
decrease in wage bill. The bill dropped 6.2 percent against the
same 1997 period to 17.8 billion yuan. 
