<HEADLINE> Jiang: Reunification Irreversible Historical Trend </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 1 (Xinhua) -- To realize the full
reunification of the motherland is an irreversible historical
trend, Chinese President Jiang Zemin said here today.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, also General Secretary of China's Communist Party
Central Committee, made the remarks here this morning at a new
year reception sponsored by the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference.
</P>
<P>
He said, "There still exist political differences between us
and the Taiwan authorities, but they can be reasonably and
properly resolved through dialogue and negotiations."
</P>
<P>
"Both sides across the Taiwan straits should further expand
exchanges and comprehensively develop the cross-straits
relationship in a bid to promote the process of the motherland's
reunification," he added.
</P>
<P>
Jiang hoped that the Taiwan authorities will cater to the
aspiration of the people, eye the circumstances in a practical
way, and have dialogue and negotiations with the mainland in an
effort to realize the early establishment of direct links of
postal, air and shipping services and trade between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
Both sides across the straits should formally end the enmity
state under the "one China" principle, he said.
</P>
<P>
He urged all patriotic Chinese to unite and firmly oppose any
splittist activities aimed at bringing about the "independence of
Taiwan" and creating "two Chinas" or "one China, one Taiwan" so as
to safeguard the motherland's territorial integrity and
sovereignty.
</P>
<P>
Through the joint efforts of all Chinese people, including the
Taiwan compatriots, the motherland's reunification should surely
be accomplished, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
On issues of Hong Kong and Macao, he continued, since the
return of Hong Kong, China has strictly observed the policy of
"one country, two systems", "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong"
and a high degree of autonomy, and supported the government of
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region to administer according to
law, thus helping Hong Kong maintain stability and prosperity
amids the Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
By December 1999, he said, China will resume the exercise of
sovereignty over Macao and this is a great event for the Chinese
nation.
</P>
<P>
"We hope both China and Portugal continue their cooperation
and the Macao compatriots play a positive role to ensure a smooth
transition and transfer of power in Macao for local stability and
development," Jiang added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
