<HEADLINE> China Spends More on Residential Buildings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 1 (Xinhua) -- China has increased its
investment in residential buildings last year, according to
figures from the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
Investment in residential buildings between January and October
reached 132.77 billion yuan (15.9 billion U.S. dollars), growing 29
percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
China's total investment in real estate development in the
January-October period amounted to 218 billion yuan (26.3 billion
U.S. dollars), up 18.4 percent on an year-on-year basis.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has carried out a series of housing
reforms to encourage citizens to buy houses and apartments on
their own, and several banks has extended loans to individual
house buyers. 
