<HEADLINE> Eight Die in Floods in Bengkulu, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Floods triggered by incessant
rains since Wednesday killed eight people and injured 13 others in
Bengkulu province, Indonesia's Sumatera island.
</P>
<P>
Most of the flood victims were gold miners. The inundation
destroyed 35 miners' houses and some gold mining equipment, Antara
News Agency reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The flood waters came from the Kerinci Seblat National Park and
caused landslides in an area measuring two hectares, a location
where local inhabitants have conducted traditional gold mining
since 1982.
</P>
<P>
Bengkulu Vice Governor Iskandar Ramis visited Ketenong Satu,
one of the flood-hit villages, on Thursday to hand over rice and
some cash to the flood victims.
</P>
<P>
The disaster was the second this week, following a landslide
which killed four people and wounded 10 others in a village last
Monday. Only two bodies were found, while the other two were
believed to be still buried in the mud. 
</P>
</TEXT>
