<HEADLINE> China Facing Strenuous Tasks in 1999: Jiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 1 (Xinhua) -- China is confronted with
strenuous tasks in reform and development in 1999, said Chinese
President Jiang Zemin here this morning.
</P>
<P>
"We should continue to make tremendous efforts in the face of
many difficulties," Jiang, also general secretary of the Chinese
Communist Party's Central Committee and chairman of the Central
Military Commission, said at a new year reception held by the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC).
</P>
<P>
The reception saw the presence of more than 400 people
including the nation's top leaders Li Peng, Zhu Rongji, Li
Ruihuan, Hu Jintao, Wei Jianxing and Li Lanqing.
</P>
<P>
Delivering a speech at the party, Jiang said that the Chinese
people, under the leadership of the Chinese Communist Party,
withstood severe tests and made new significant achievements in
reform and development during the past year.
</P>
<P>
To deal with the impact of the deepening Asian financial crisis
and the worsening international economic situation, China has
taken decisive measures to stimulate domestic demand and expand
construction of infrastructure facilities by making use of
macro-economic control measures such as financial, monetary and
investment policies, which has helped the national economy
maintain a rapid growth, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Describing the year 1999 as having a unique significance in the
development history of China, Jiang said that the country will
continue to promote reform and opening to the outside world, and
mainly rely on expanding domestic demand to facilitate economic
growth.
</P>
<P>
"While it is necessary and also attainable to keep an adequate
rapid economic growth this year, much attention should be paid to
maintaining a coordinated development and concentrating on quality
and efficiency," he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also said that it is necessary to attach great importance
to and properly handle contradictions among the people and various
kinds of social problems and crack down sternly on all kinds of
sabotage activities by hostile forces both at home and abroad, so
as to ensure social and political stability of the nation.
</P>
<P>
He called on people of all walks of life to overcome the
difficulties and strive for new progress under the leadership of
the Chinese Communist Party in the new year.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee and
Chairman of the CPPCC National Committee, presided over today's
party.  
</P>
