<HEADLINE> Citizens in Shenzhen Earn Most in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 1 (Xinhua) -- The average income of urban
households in Shenzhen ranked first in 35 of China's major cities
in September, according to figures from the National Bureau of
Statistics.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the average per capita monthly income in
Shenzhen hit 1,578.6 yuan in September, and the per capita monthly
disposable income reached 1,553.4 yuan. The city's per capita
monthly living expenditure stood at 1,567.5 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Following Shenzhen are Guangzhou and Xiamen in per capita
monthly income and monthly disposable income.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen, neighboring to Hong Kong, is China's first special
economic zone. 
