<HEADLINE> Fewer Firecracker-Related Injuries Reported in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Only 247 injuries had been
reported so far in firecracker-related incidents in the
Philippines during the new year celebrations, according to a
monitoring report by the Department of Health Friday.
</P>
<P>
The figure was about 28 percent of the 1,147 injuries for 1997,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
The monitoring report covered the period from 06:00 (22:00 GMT
Wednesday) Thursday up to 06:00 (22:00 GMT Thursday) Friday.
</P>
<P>
The report also said that 14 people were either shot or hit by
stray bullets, also down significantly from the 31 stray-bullet
injuries for 1997.
</P>
<P>
The big drop in firecrackers-related injuries was attributed by
the Philippine National Police to the effective coordination among
the government, hospitals, the media and the public. 
