<HEADLINE> China's Real Estate Prices Rising </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 1 (Xinhua) -- China's real estate prices have
gone up in the third quarter of 1998, according to the latest
figures released by the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The house selling price index of 35 major cities rose by 1.3
percent between July and September over the same period last
year. The land rent price index went up by 3.1 percent and the
house rent price index rose by 0.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
Northwest China's Yinchuan City, capital of Ningxia Hui
Autonomous Region, ranked first in house selling price index, with
its index rising by 15.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
The highest land rent price index was in Shijiazhuang, capital
city of north China's Hebei Province, jumping up 30 percent on a
year-on-year basis.
</P>
<P>
Southeast China's Fuzhou city, capital of coastal Fujian
Province, had the country's biggest increase of 14.8 percent in
house rent price index. 
</P>
