<HEADLINE> Vietnam Produces 11.2 Million Tons of Coal in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 1 (Xinhua) -- The Vietnam Coal Corporation
(VINACOAL) turned out 11.2 million tons of coal and sold 10.5
million tons for 2.8 trillion VN dong (202 million U.S. dollars)
in 1998, according to Vietnam News Agency.
</P>
<P>
Despite adverse impacts of the regional financial crisis, the
corporation exported 3 million tons of coal this year. Japan was
the largest importer by purchasing 1.4 million tons, followed by
West European countries with 540,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
VINACOAL has won a 14-year contract to export 200,000 tons of
dust coal per year to Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Big domestic consumers of coal included family households in
remote areas with 4.5 million tons, and the power industry with
2.3 million tons.
</P>
<P>
The corporation plans to turn out 10.56 million tons and sell
11.5 million tons to domestic and foreign markets in 1999.
</P>
