<HEADLINE> Thai Border Patrol Officer Shot Dead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Gunmen, believed to be
separatists, shot dead a border patrol officer in broad daylight
in Southern Thailand, a police source said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The source said a group of heavily-armed men driving a pick-up
truck and two motorcycles chased the officer from his house in
Narathiwat Province on Wednesday and fired several shots at close
range at a deserted route.
</P>
<P>
The officer, Pol Sgt Masawree Binwae-arong, 31, was found lying
in a pool of blood beside his motorcycle. He sustained serious
gunshot wounds and died on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Police believed the gunmen might be members of a separatist
group in Southern Thailand, populated by Muslims. A series of
attacks against policemen and civilians had been reported before.
</P>
<P>
A manhunt for the gunmen was still going on, said the source,
requesting anonymity. 
