<HEADLINE> Myanmar Presents Motion Picture Awards for 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar's Ministry of Information
has presented 12 motion picture gold star awards of 11 categories
for 1997 to artists in the country.
</P>
<P>
The 12 awards from 4 films out of 11, which were presented
Thursday, include the best film award, the best director award,
the best actor and actress awards and the best editor award.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar Minister of Information Maj. Gen. Kyi Aung told the
presentation ceremony that the points which were taken into
consideration for the awards are the goal set by the state, the
national policy, national culture and national interest, adding
that the points that should be avoided in producing the motion
pictures were also taken into account.
</P>
<P>
He admitted that the strength of producing Myanmar movies is
decreasing year after year. In 1996, 25 movies came out to vie for
best film awards in the respective categories, while there were 43
in 1994.
</P>
<P>
He warned that a decline in production of high-standard Myanmar
movies would not only give space to foreign films but would also
help promote the market for foreign films.
</P>
<P>
He urged the producers to strive to help Myanmar films gain
markets abroad.
</P>
<P>
He also said that in 1998 only 15 new Myanmar films would be
produced.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar formed the Appraisal Board for Raising the Standard of
Myanmar Motion Picture in 1952 and has presented 209 best awards
of 11 categories of films screened. 
</P>
</TEXT>
