<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 1 (Xinhua) -- Three people were hurt by stray
bullets in the Philippine capital of Manila on the New Year's eve
although there were less firecracker blasting incidents compared
to the previous year, hospital authorities said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Doctors of the Philippine General Hospital said they admitted
Friday morning a 26-year-old construction worker from San Andres
Bukid, Manila, for injuries in the right arm caused by a stray
bullet.
</P>
<P>
At the Ospital ng Maynila, two victims of stray bullets were
admitted.
</P>
<P>
The victims, both from Binondo, Manila, were hit in the right
arm and right leg, respectively, hospital authorities said.
</P>
<P>
The authorities have not yet reported the number of victims of
firecracker blasting. In the past years, hundreds of people were
hurt in firecracker blasting incidents in the country on the New
Year's eve. 
