Andres Pastrana will start an official visit to Cuba on January
14 for talks with Cuban President Fidel Castro, in the first
official visit to the country by a Colombian president, a spokesm
an of the Presidential Office said.
</P>
<P>
Pastrana said two weeks ago that Castro supports the process
of peace of his government with the rebel guerrillas.
</P>
<P>
Colombia broke diplomatic relations with Cuba in 1961 and
resumed them in 1975, but suspended them again between 1981 and
1992, because of an alleged support and training of the Colombian
guerrillas by Cuba. 
</P>
</TEXT>
