because of the yield obtained by the Madrid stock market with a
37 percent increase and because of "the meaning of the stock
market for the financing of the Spanish economy."
</P>
<P>
The Madrid Stock Exchange president said that 1998 also ends
with "a growing degree of internationalization of the market."
</P>
<P>
He said that the year 1999 starts with a good economic
condition, but refused to make forecasts about possible
performances of the stock market. 
