<HEADLINE> Kenyan Star Wins San Silvestre Road Race Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, December 31 (Xinhua) -- Paul Tergat of Kenya
won the San Silvestre road race for the third time here on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Tergat, winner in the race in 1995 and 1996, clocked 44
minutes 48 seconds to cover the 15-kilometre course.
</P>
<P>
The Kenyan Air Force officer, a former 10,000 meter world
record holder and silver medalist at the 1996 Olympic and 1997
World Championship over the distance, made his break three
kilometers from the finish.
</P>
<P>
The 29-year-old, who still holds the half marathon world best
time, pulled away to beat South African Hendrick Ramaala to
second the second place at 45:05, just ahead of another Kenyan,
Elijah Lagat in 45:08.
</P>
<P>
Last year's winner Emerson Iser Bem of Brazil came sixth,
almost a minute behind Tergat.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslav track star Olivera Jevtic won the women's race at
her first attempt, clocking 51 minutes 35 seconds over the same
distance.
</P>
<P>
Martha Tenorio of Ecuador was 20 seconds behind, and Kenya's
Jane Ngotho third, 1:07 off the pace. 
</P>
</TEXT>
