<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2100 GMT, December 31 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY -- Iraq and the United States are not heading for
"an imminent fresh crisis," said a Saudi Arabian official
Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
The current confrontations in the no-fly zones in northern
and southern Iraq "is just due to a misunderstanding," said Prince
Sultan Ibn Abdul-Aziz, Saudi Second Deputy Prime Minister, the
Kuwait News Agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He said that his country supports the call for lifting the
eight-year-old U.N. sanctions on Iraq, but "this is conditional to
agreeing and implementing the U.N. resolutions to serve their
country and its interest." (BC-Saudi Arabia-Iraq-Crisis)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- U.S. Embassy in Tel Aviv closed on Thursday after
Ambassador Edward Walker received "credible threats."
</P>
<P>
"The embassy received a credible and specific threat and as a
result the ambassador thought it prudent to close the embassy
today while we investigate with the appropriate authorities," said
embassy spokesman Larry Schwartz.
</P>
<P>
An Israeli security source, requesting anonymity, said the
threats were aimed at the embassy staff. Israeli radio said the
life of Walker was threatened.
</P>
<P>
Schwartz said it has not been decided on when the embassy will
reopen. (BC-U.S.-Embassy-Closes)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
AMMAN -- Over 200 Jordanians staged a sit-in protest in front
of the U.S. embassy in Amman Thursday morning, demanding an
immediate end to U.S. military actions against Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Riot police did not intervene in the peaceful protest, which
went on from 11 a.m. to 12 a.m. local time.
</P>
<P>
The protest was organized by the non-governmental Popular
Committee for Supporting Iraq, which had also called for lifting
the sanctions imposed on Iraq following its 1990 invasion of
Kuwait. (BC-Jordan-Protest-Iraq)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NICOSIA -- Cyprus President Glafcos Clerides on Thursday
called on the international community to act more decisively and
to fulfill its responsibilities in resolving the Cyprus issue.
</P>
<P>
In his New Year message, Clerides said that Cyprus' goal of
joining the European Union (EU) is beginning to be realised with
the opening of substantive talks in November.
(BC-Cyprus-President-Message) 
</P>
